
- var traits = [['Cautious','Curious'],['Organized','Easy Going'],['Outgoing','Reserved'],['Sensitive','Confident'],['Compassionate','Analytical']]
	div.your-personality
		div.description
			p
				span.me #{user.name}
				| , your Twitter personality is...
	.row.avatars-row
		.col-sm-4.col-xs-12.me
			div.avatar.text-right.img-circle
				div.second-border.img-circle
					div.third-border.img-circle
						img.me(src='#{user.image.replace("_normal","_400x400")}')
			div.text-center
				p.avatar-name
					a(href="https://twitter.com/#{user.username}") @#{user.username}
		.col-sm-4.text-center.col-xs-12
			div.similarity
				div.left-bar
					div
				div.right-bar
					div
				div.similarity-percentage
					h1.cel_distance
			h4.similar-to
				| similar to
				br
				span.cel_name
		.col-sm-4.col-xs-12.celebrity
			div.avatar.text-right.img-circle
				div.second-border.img-circle
					div.third-border.img-circle
						img.cel_image.celebrity
			div.text-center
				p.avatar-name
					a.cel_username
each trait, i in traits
	.row.trait-row
		.col-md-3
			p.text-right #{trait[0]}
		.col-md-3.col-md-push-6
			p.text-left #{trait[1]}
		.col-md-6.col-md-pull-3
			div.measuring-bar
				div.point.mep(style='left:calc(#{user_profile[i].value * 100 }%)')
				div.point.celebrityp(id='trait_#{i}')
div.more-info
	a.how-it-works-link(href="javascript:void(0);") How'd we get this?
div.social-media
	div.social-media-buttons
		h6 Share this result:
		div.twitter
			a.twitter-share-button(href="https://twitter.com/share", data-text="#{user.name}'s personality is #{Math.round(similar_celebs[0].distance * 100)}% similar to #{similar_celebs[0].user.name}'s! #CelebMatch #IBMWatson", data-hashtags="PersonalityInsights")
				| Tweet
